ro in this fight, but thought it was worth sharing this new </span><em>Time=
</em><span> profile of Argentinian President Javier Milei. Milei certainly =
has his critics and it's frankly is too early to tell if his economic plans=
 will pan out for Argentina in the long run, but the guy is doing what he p=
romised to do and the early results speak for themself. Inflation is down. =
The currency is devalued by 50%.  Spending is down. Argentina ran a surplus=
 in Q1 &#8216;24, the country's first quarterly surplus since 2008.&#160;Mi=
lei is delivering on his plan, whether you or the Argentinian people want h=
im to. Milei promised change, and change is what he is delivering.</span></=
p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; m=
argin: 0 0 20px 0;">Whether you agree with or like Milei is besides the poi=
nt. The point is that real change is possible within democratic governments=
, and that change can (and in many cases should!) happen quickly.</p><p sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;">On this Memorial Day Weekend, the story of Argentina serves as =
a good reminder. In the early 20th century, it was one of the top 10 wealth=
iest countries in the world and experienced long periods of political stabi=
lity. Today it&#8217;s the ~75th richest country in the world. What happene=
d? To overgeneralize: socialism and mismanagement. </p><p style=3D"color: r=
gb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Ca=
pitalism and democracy are worth fighting for. We&#8217;re thankful that ge=
nerations of American men and women, much braver than me, agree with that s=
tatement and have paid the highest price protecting those ideals.</p><p sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;">Enjoy the long weekend, support the troops, and God Bless Ameri=
ca.</p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;"><hr style=3D"back=
